02/10/2014 07:39 PM
Core Responsibilities:This individual will play a key role in designing, developing and characterizing sensing systems.Applicant must be familiar with MEMS sensor technology such as motion sensor performance metrics, magnetic sensor usage and limitations, acoustic, pressure, optical and environmental sensing, as well as manufacturing technologies of such sensors.Develop measurement methods and equipment that are repeatable, reproducible, and automated as appropriate to enable thorough validation coverage of sensors on tight development schedules.Diagnose engineering issues with true scientific method, driving to definitive root cause, in close collaboration with cross-functional team members.Identify, create and document new sensing system metrics and specifications that deliver performance that matter to customer perception. Work with sensing users to correlate performance metrics.Performance matching across multiple sources for sensors. Work with suppliers to identify issues of matching to our specs. Synchronize new part evaluation.Analyze trade-offs among performance, manufacturability, size, schedule and cost.Simulate sensing system performance and error sensitivities.Support engineering build activities with performance validation measurements, yield optimization and failure analysis coordination. Be able to work with suppliers on yield issues affecting sensors. Travel to supplier facilities for new sensor bring up and manufacturing sites for production issues as needed.Help improve ERS documents for sensors. Work with internal teams to assure that documents meet needs.Prepare and deliver presentations to clearly communicate technical status, risks and mitigation strategies for ongoing sensing system programs.BS Engineering/MS Engineering is required
